{
  "texts": [
    "Here, again, if a nonzero MHS equilibrium is used, the operator defined by Eq. 79 applies to the magnetic field perturbation B 1, not to the full vector B 0 + B 1, while for the zeroequilibrium case it applies to the full variable, B = B 1.",
    "The artificial diffusivity term in the total energy equation is composed of three components: viscous and Ohmic heating terms, and artificial heat conduction (Vögler et al., 2005),",
    "where c p is the specific heat at constant pressure.",
    "In the internal energy equation, the artificial conductivity term remains the same, while the other two are modified accordingly,",
    "where: stands for tensor double contraction."
  ]
}